                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.48/828: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Weddell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-01-08T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 8, 1941—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>13. Refer Department’s 12, January 7, 6 p.m. The plan for shipment of supplies
                    for relief of children in unoccupied France has been made public by the Ministry
                    of Economic Warfare in London. Accordingly, the American Red Cross will today
                    make public announcement of its plans for shipment of flour and milk products to
                    Spain in conjunction with the relief project in unoccupied France.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
